.TH observer 3 "observer 2.18.2" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
observer \- A GUI tool for observing an Erlang system.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Observer is a graphical tool for observing the characteristics of Erlang systems. The tool Observer displays system information, application supervisor trees, process information, ETS tables, Mnesia tables, and contains a front end for Erlang tracing with module \fIttb\fR.

.PP
For details about how to get started, see the \fIUser's Guide\fR.

.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBstart() -> ok | {error, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Starts the Observer GUI. To stop the tool, close the window or call \fIstop/0\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBstart(Node :: node() | [node()]) -> ok | {error, term()}.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Starts the Observer GUI and tries to connect it to \fINode\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBstart_and_wait() -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Starts the Observer GUI and only return when it is either stopped or the window is closed


.RE
.B
\fBstart_and_wait(Node :: node() | [node()]) -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Starts the Observer GUI and only return when it is either stopped or the window is closed, connects it directly to \fINode\fR like \fIstart/1\fR.


.RE
.B
\fBstop() -> ok.\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Stops the Observer GUI.


.RE
